            ingat: '"EMR = Elastic + Master node + Ramai-pekerja: Elastic cluster, Master node (ketua agih kerja), Ramai pekerja (Core/Task). Hadoop/Spark, kau urus cluster (BUKAN serverless)."',
            gunaUntuk: 'Process petabyte-scale data with Spark, Hadoop, Hive, Presto вҖ” full control',
            fungsi: 'Managed cluster platform untuk big data frameworks (Spark, Hadoop, Hive, Presto, HBase). Kau choose cluster size, instance types, frameworks. Cluster ada 3 jenis node: Master (urus cluster), Core (run task + simpan HDFS), Task (run task sahaja, no HDFS). EMRFS benarkan EMR guna S3 sebagai storage layer вҶ’ decouple compute dari storage. Lebih control dari Glue вҖ” untuk complex/custom big-data jobs.',
            sebabApa: "EMR wujud sebab proses data berskala petabyte (log, ML, transform berat) guna satu EC2 mustahil вҖ” kau perlu cluster Spark/Hadoop, tapi setup & urus cluster Hadoop sendiri (provision, config, scale, patch) itu sangat susah. EMR managed-kan cluster big-data tu: kau pilih saiz/framework, AWS handle setup, dan boleh guna Spot + transient cluster (mati lepas job, data kekal di S3) untuk jimat besar.",
            sifir: ["EMR = managed cluster big-data (Spark/Hadoop/Hive/Presto/HBase) вҖ” kau urus cluster (BUKAN serverless).", "3 node: Master (urus), Core (task + HDFS data), Task (task sahaja).", "Spot: Task = selamat (no data). Core = berisiko (pegang HDFS). Master = jangan Spot langsung.", "EMRFS = guna S3 sebagai storage вҶ’ transient cluster (mati lepas job, data kekal di S3).", "EMR vs Glue: EMR = full control framework. Glue = serverless ETL, no cluster.", "EMR vs Redshift: EMR = kod (Spark/Python) atas data mentah. Redshift = SQL atas data kemas (OLAP)."],
